20606.Message: If a <species> is located in a <compartment> whose 'spatialDimensions' has value '2', then that <species> definition can only set 'spatialSizeUnits' to a value of 'area', 'dimensionless', or the identifier of a <unitDefinition> derived from either 'metre' (with an 'exponent' value of '2') or 'dimensionless'.
20606.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'spatialSizeUnits' attribute of a two-dimensional compartment

20607.Message: If a <species> is located in a <compartment> whose 'spatialDimensions' has value '3', then that <species> definition can only set 'spatialSizeUnits' to a value of 'volume', 'litre', 'dimensionless', or the identifier of a <unitDefinition> derived from either 'litre', 'metre' (with an 'exponent' value of '3') or 'dimensionless'.
20607.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'spatialSizeUnits' attribute of a three-dimensional compartment

20608.Message:
The value of a <species>'s 'units' attribute is restricted. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.4
20608.ShortMessage: Invalid value for a Species 'units' attribute

20609.Message:
A <species> cannot set values for both 'initialConcentration' and 'initialAmount' because they are mutually exclusive.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.4
20609.ShortMessage: Cannot set both 'initialConcentration' and 'initialAmount' attributes simultaneously

20610.Message:
A <species>'s quantity cannot be determined simultaneously by both reactions and rules. More formally, if the identifier of a <species> definition having 'boundaryCondition'='false' and 'constant'='false' is referenced by a <speciesReference> anywhere in a model, then this identifier cannot also appear as the value of a 'variable' in an <assignmentRule> or a <rateRule>.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.6
20610.ShortMessage: Cannot use a non-boundary species in both reactions and rules simultaneously

20611.Message:
A <species> having boundaryCondition='false' cannot appear as a reactant or product in any reaction if that Species also has constant='true'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.6
20611.ShortMessage: Cannot use a constant, non-boundary species as a reactant or product

20612.Message: The value of 'speciesType' in a <species> definition must be the identifier of an existing <speciesType>.
20612.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'speciesType' attribute of a species

20613.Message: There cannot be more than one species of a given <speciesType> in the same compartment of a model. More formally, for any given compartment, there cannot be more than one <species> definition in which both of the following hold simultaneously: (i) the <species>' 'compartment' value is set to that compartment's identifier and (ii) the <species>' 'speciesType' is set the same value as the 'speciesType' of another <species> that also sets its 'compartment' to that compartment identifier.
20613.ShortMessage: Cannot have multiple species of the same species type in the same compartment

20614.Message:
The 'compartment' attribute in a <species> is mandatory. A <species> definition in a model must include a value for this attribute. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.3

20615.Message: The 'spatialSizeUnits' attribute on <species>, previously available in SBML Level 2 versions prior to Version 3, has been removed as of SBML Level 2 Version 3.
20615.ShortMessage: Attribute 'spatialSizeUnits' is not supported in this Level+Version of SBML

20616.Message:
If the attribute 'substanceUnits' in a Species object has not been set, then the unit of measurement associated with the species' quantity is determined by the value of the enclosing Model object's 'substanceUnits' attribute. If neither the Species object's 'substanceUnits' attribute nor the enclosing Model object's 'substanceUnits' attribute are set, then the unit of that species' quantity is undefined.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.5
20616.ShortMessage: No substance units defined for the species

20617.Message:
The value of the attribute 'conversionFactor' on a Species object must be the identifier of an existing Parameter object defined in the enclosing Model object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.7

20623.Message:
A Species object must have the required attributes 'id', 'compartment', 'hasOnlySubstanceUnits', 'boundaryCondition' and 'constant', and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name', 'initialAmount', 'initialConcentration', 'substanceUnits' and 'conversionFactor'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Species object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6
20623.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on Species object

20701.Message:
The 'units' in a <Parameter> definition must be a value chosen from among the following: a predefined unit (e.g., 'substance', 'time', etc.), the identifier of a <UnitDefinition> in the model, or one of the base units in SBML (e.g., 'litre', 'mole', 'metre', etc.)
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.7.3
20701.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'units' attribute of a Parameter object

20702.Message:
If the attribute 'units' on a given Parameter object has not been set, then the unit of measurement associated with that parameter's value is undefined.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.7.3
20702.ShortMessage: No units defined for the parameter

20705.Message:
A Parameter object referenced by the attribute 'conversionFactor' on a Species or Model object must have a value of 'true' for its attribute 'constant'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.6.7
20705.ShortMessage: A conversion factor must reference a Parameter object declared to be a constant

20706.Message:
A Parameter object must have the required attributes 'id' and 'constant', and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name', 'value' and 'units'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Parameter object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.7
20706.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on Parameter object

20801.Message:
The value of 'symbol' in an <initialAssignment> definition must be the identifier of an existing <compartment>, <species>, or <parameter> defined in the model or <speciesReference> in Level 3.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20801.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'symbol' attribute of an InitialAssignment object

20802.Message:
A given identifier cannot appear as the value of more than one 'symbol' field across the set of <initialAssignment>s in a model.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20802.ShortMessage: Multiple initial assignments for the same 'symbol' value are not allowed

20803.Message:
The value of a 'symbol' field in any <initialAssignment> definition cannot also appear as the value of a 'variable' field in an <assignmentRule>. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20803.ShortMessage: Cannot set a value using both an initial assignment and an assignment rule simultaneously

20804.Message:
An InitialAssignment object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20804.ShortMessage: An InitialAssignment object may contain one <math> element

20805.Message:
An InitialAssignment object must have the required attribute 'symbol' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an InitialAssignment object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.8
20805.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on an InitialAssignment object

20806.Message: The identifier given as the value of a 'symbol' attribute in any <initialAssignment> definition cannot be the identifier of a <compartment> with a 'spatialDimensions' value of 0.

20901.Message:
The value of an <assignmentRule>'s 'variable' must be the identifier of an existing <compartment>, <species>, globally-defined <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference>. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.3
20901.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'variable' attribute of an AssignmentRule object

20902.Message:
The value of a <rateRule>'s 'variable' must be the identifier of an existing <compartment>, <species>, globally-defined <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference>. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.4
20902.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the 'variable' attribute of a RateRule object

20903.Message:
Any <compartment>, <species>, <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference> whose identifier is the value of a 'variable' attribute in an <assignmentRule>, must have a value of 'false' for 'constant'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.3
20903.ShortMessage: An assignment rule cannot assign an entity declared to be constant

20904.Message:
Any <compartment>, <species>, <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference> whose identifier is the value of a 'variable' attribute in an <rateRule>, must have a value of 'false' for 'constant'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.4
20904.ShortMessage: A rate rule cannot assign an entity declared to be constant

20906.Message:
There must not be circular dependencies in the combined set of <initialAssignment>, <assignmentRule> and <kineticLaw> definitions in a model. Each of these constructs has the effect of assigning a value to an identifier (i.e. the identifier given in the field 'symbol' in <initialAssignment>, the field 'variable' in <assignmentRule>, and the field 'id' on the <kineticLaw>'s enclosing <reaction>). Each of these constructs computes the value using a mathematical formula. The formula for a given identifier cannot make reference to a second identifier whose own definition depends directly or indirectly on the first identifier.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9.5
20906.ShortMessage: Circular dependencies involving rules and reactions are not permitted

20907.Message:
Every AssignmentRule, RateRule and AlgebraicRule object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9
20907.ShortMessage: A rule object may contain one <math> element

20908.Message:
An AssignmentRule object must have the required attribute 'variable' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an AssignmentRule object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9
20908.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on an AssignmentRule object

20909.Message:
A RateRule object must have the required attribute 'variable' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a RateRule object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9
20909.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on a RateRule object

20910.Message:
An AlgebraicRule object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an AlgebraicRule object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.9
20910.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on an AlgebraicRule object

20911.Message: The value of a <rateRule> or <assignmentRule>'s 'variable' attribute must not be the identifier of a <compartment> with a 'spatialDimensions' value of 0.

20912.Message: There must not be circular dependencies in the combined set of <rateRule> and <kineticLaw> objects in the model.  Each of these constructs has the effect of assigning a value to the time derivative of one or more identifiers (i.e., the identifier given in the attribute 'variable' in the <rateRule>, and the identifier of any <species> referenced by a <speciesReference> in the same <reaction> as the <kineticLaw>).  Each of these constructs computes the value using a mathematical formula.  The formula used to calculate the time derivative of a given identifier cannot make reference to a second identifier whose own definition depends directly or indirectly on a 'rateOf' 'csymbol' for the first identifier.
20912.ShortMessage: Circular dependencies are not permitted in RateRule and KineticLaw objects

21001.Message:
A <constraint>'s <math> expression must evaluate to a value of type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10
21001.ShortMessage: A Constraint object's <math> must evaluate to a Boolean value

21002.Message: The order of subelements within <constraint> must be the following: <math>, <message>. The <message> element is optional, but if present, must follow the <math> element.
21002.ShortMessage: Subobjects inside the Constraint object are not in the prescribed order

21003.Message: The contents of the <message> element in a <constraint> must be explicitly placed in the XHTML XML namespace.
21003.ShortMessage: A Constraint's Message subobject must be in the XHTML XML namespace

21004.Message:
The contents of the <message> element must not contain an XML declaration (i.e., a string of the form "<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>" or similar).
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10.2
21004.ShortMessage: XML declarations are not permitted within Constraint's Message objects

21005.Message:
The contents of the <message> element must not contain an XML DOCTYPE declaration (i.e., a string beginning with the characters "<!DOCTYPE". 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10.2
21005.ShortMessage: XML DOCTYPE elements are not permitted within Constraint's Message objects

21006.Message: The XHTML content inside a <constraint>'s <message> element can only take one of the following general forms: (1) a complete XHTML document beginning with the element <html> and ending with </html>; (2) the "body" portion of a document beginning with the element <body> and ending with </body>; or (3) XHTML content that is permitted within a <body> ... </body> elements.
21006.ShortMessage: Invalid content for a Constraint object's Message object

21007.Message:
A <constraint> object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10
21007.ShortMessage: A Constraint object may contain one <math> element

21008.Message:
A <constraint> object may contain at most one <message> subobject.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10
21008.ShortMessage: A Constraint object can only have one Message subobject

21009.Message:
A <constraint> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Constraint object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.10
21009.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on Constraint object

21101.Message:
A <reaction> definition must contain at least one <speciesReference>, either in its <listOfReactants> or its <listOfProducts>. A reaction without any reactant or product species is not permitted, regardless of whether the reaction has any modifier species.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11.3
21101.ShortMessage: Cannot have a reaction with neither reactants nor products

21102.Message: The order of subelements within <reaction> must be the following: <listOfReactants> (optional), <listOfProducts> (optional), <listOfModifiers> (optional), <kineticLaw>.
21102.ShortMessage: Subobjects inside the Reaction object are not in the prescribed order

21103.Message:
The following containers are all optional in a <reaction>, but if any is present, it must not be empty: <listOfReactants>, <listOfProducts>, <listOfModifiers>, <kineticLaw>.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21103.ShortMessage: Reaction components, if present, cannot be empty

21104.Message:
The list of reactants (<listOfReactants>) and list of products (<listOfProducts>) in a <reaction> can only contain <speciesReference> elements.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21104.ShortMessage: Invalid object found in the list of reactants or products

21105.Message:
The list of modifiers (<listOfModifiers>) in a <reaction> can only contain <modifierSpeciesReference> elements.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21105.ShortMessage: Invalid object found in the list of modifiers

21106.Message:
A <reaction> object may contain at most one of each of the following elements: <listOfReactants>, <listOfProducts>, <listOfModifiers>, and <kineticLaw>.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21106.ShortMessage: A Reaction object can only contain one of each allowed type of object

21107.Message:
The value of the attribute 'compartment' in a <reaction> object is optional, but if present, must be the identifier of an existing Compartment object defined in the model.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11.1
21107.ShortMessage: Invalid value for the Reaction 'compartment' attribute

21110.Message:
A <reaction> object must have the required attributes 'id', 'reversible' and 'fast', and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name' and 'compartment'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Reaction object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21110.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute for a Reaction object

21111.Message:
The value of a <speciesReference> 'species' attribute must be the identifier of an existing <species> in the model. 
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11.3
21111.ShortMessage: Invalid 'species' attribute value in SpeciesReference object

21113.Message: A <speciesReference> must not have a value for both 'stoichiometry' and 'stoichiometryMath'; they are mutually exclusive.
21113.ShortMessage: The 'stoichiometry' attribute and StoichiometryMath subobject are mutually exclusive

21116.Message:
A <speciesReference> object must have the required attributes 'species' and 'constant', and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name' 'id' and 'stoichiometry'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <speciesReference> object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21116.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the SpeciesReference object

21117.Message:
A <modifierSpeciesReference> object must have the required attribute 'species' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'id' and 'name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <modifierSpeciesReference> object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21117.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ModifierSpeciesReference object

21121.Message:
All species referenced in the <kineticLaw> formula of a given reaction must first be declared using <speciesReference> or <modifierSpeciesReference>. More formally, if a <species> identifier appears in a <ci> element of a <reaction>'s <kineticLaw> formula, that same identifier must also appear in at least one <speciesReference> or <modifierSpeciesReference> in the <reaction> definition.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11.5
21121.ShortMessage: Unknown species referenced in the kinetic law <math> formula

21122.Message: The order of subelements within <kineticLaw> must be the following: <math>, <listOfParameters>. The <listOfParameters> is optional, but if present, must follow <math>.
21122.ShortMessage: Incorrect ordering of components in the KineticLaw object

21123.Message:
If present, the <listOfParameters> in a <kineticLaw> must not be an empty list.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21123.ShortMessage: The list of parameters, if present, cannot be empty

21124.Message: The 'constant' attribute on a <parameter> local to a <kineticLaw> cannot have a value other than 'true'. The values of parameters local to <kineticLaw> definitions cannot be changed, and therefore they are always constant.
21124.ShortMessage: Parameters local to a KineticLaw object must have a 'constant' attribute value of 'true'

21125.Message: The 'substanceUnits' attribute on <kineticLaw>, previously available in SBML Level 1 and Level 2 Version 1, has been removed as of SBML Level 2 Version 2. In SBML Level 2 Version 2, the substance units of a reaction rate expression are those of the global 'substance' units of the model.
21125.ShortMessage: Attribute 'substanceUnits' is not supported in this Level+Version of SBML

21126.Message: The 'timeUnits' attribute on <kineticLaw>, previously available in SBML Level 1 and Level 2 Version 1, has been removed as of SBML Level 2 Version 2. In SBML Level 2 Version 2, the time units of a reaction rate expression are those of the global 'time' units of the model.
21126.ShortMessage: Attribute 'timeUnits' is not supported in this Level+Version of SBML

21127.Message:
A KineticLaw object may contain at most one ListOfLocalParameters container object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21127.ShortMessage: Only one ListOfLocalParameters object is permitted within a KineticLaw object

21128.Message:
Apart from the general Notes and Annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML components, a ListOfLocalParameters container object may only contain LocalParameter objects.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.2.8
21128.ShortMessage: Only LocalParameter, Notes and Annotation objects are allowed in ListOfLocalParameter objects

21129.Message:
A ListOfLocalParameters object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a ListOfLocalParameters object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21129.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ListOfLocalParameters object

21130.Message:
A KineticLaw object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21130.ShortMessage: Only one <math> element is allowed in a KineticLaw object

21131.Message: All species referenced in the <stoichiometryMath> formula of a given reaction must first be declared using <speciesReference> or <modifierSpeciesReference>. More formally, if a <species> identifier appears in a <ci> element of a <reaction>'s <stoichiometryMath> formula, that same identifier must also appear in at least one <speciesReference> or <modifierSpeciesReference> in the <reaction> definition.
21131.ShortMessage: Unknown species referenced in the StoichiometryMath object's <math> formula

21132.Message:
A KineticLaw object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a KineticLaw object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21132.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the KineticLaw object

21150.Message:
A ListOfSpeciesReferences object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a ListOfSpeciesReferences object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21150.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ListOfSpeciesReferences object

21151.Message:
A ListOfModifierSpeciesReferences object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a ListOfModifierSpeciesReferences object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21151.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ListOfModifiers object

21152.Message: The value of the 'fast' attribute should be 'false', as the attribute has been deprecated.

21172.Message:
A LocalParameter object must have the required attribute 'id' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'name', 'value' and 'units'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a LocalParameter object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.11
21172.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the LocalParameter object

21173.Message:
[Although SBML Level 3 Version 1 does not explicitly define the following as an error, other Levels and/or Versions of SBML do.] 
The 'id' attribute of a <localParameter> object must not be the same as the 'species' attribute of any <speciesReference> in the same <reaction>.
21173.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the LocalParameter object

21201.Message:
An <event> object must have a 'trigger'. In SBML Level 3 Version 2 this rule was relaxed to stating that an <event> object must have at most one 'trigger' element.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12.2
21201.ShortMessage: The Event object is missing a Trigger subobject

21202.Message:
An <event>'s <trigger> expression must evaluate to a value of type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12.2
21202.ShortMessage: A Trigger object's <math> expression must evaluate to a Boolean value

21203.Message:
An <event> object must have at least one <eventAssignment> object in its <listOfEventAssignments>.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21203.ShortMessage: The Event object is missing an EventAssignment subobject

21204.Message: The value of an <event>'s 'timeUnits' attribute must be 'time', 'second', 'dimensionless', or the identifier of a <unitDefinition> derived from either 'second' (with an 'exponent' value of '1') or 'dimensionless'.
21204.ShortMessage: Units referenced by 'timeUnits' attribute are not compatible with units of time

21205.Message: The order of subelements within <event> must be the following: <trigger>, <delay>, <listOfEventAssignments>. The <delay> element is optional, but if present, must follow <trigger>.
21205.ShortMessage: Incorrect ordering of components in Event object

21206.Message:
If an <event>'s 'useValuesFromTriggerTime' attribute has the value 'false', then the <event> must contain a <delay> element.  The implication of 'useValuesFromTriggerTime=false' is that there is a delay between the time of trigger and the time of value assignments performed by the <event>.  
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21206.ShortMessage: Attribute 'useValuesFromTriggerTime'='false', but the Event object does not define a delay

21207.Message:
If an Event object contains a Delay subobject, then the Event must have a value for the attribute 'useValuesFromTriggerTime'.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21207.ShortMessage: The use of a Delay object requires the Event attribute 'useValuesFromTriggerTime'

21209.Message:
A Trigger object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21209.ShortMessage: A Trigger object may have one <math> element

21210.Message:
A Delay object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21210.ShortMessage: A Delay object may have one <math> element

21211.Message:
The value of the attribute 'variable' in an <eventAssignment> can only be the identifier of a <compartment>, <species>, model-wide <parameter> definition, or <speciesReference> in Level 3.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12.4
21211.ShortMessage: Invalid 'variable' attribute value in Event object

21212.Message:
Any <compartment>, <species>, <parameter>, or (in Level 3) <speciesReference> definition whose identifier is used as the value of 'variable' in an <eventAssignment> must have a value of 'false' for its 'constant' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12.4
21212.ShortMessage: An EventAssignment object cannot assign to a component having attribute 'constant'='true'

21213.Message:
An EventAssignment object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21213.ShortMessage: An EventAssignment object may have one <math> element

21214.Message:
An EventAssignment object must have the required attribute 'variable' and may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an EventAssignment object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21214.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the EventAssignment object

21221.Message:
An Event object may contain at most one Delay object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21221.ShortMessage: An Event object can only have one Delay subobject

21222.Message:
An Event object may contain at most one ListOfEventAssignments object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21222.ShortMessage: An Event object can only have one ListOfEventAssignments subobject

21223.Message:
Apart from the general Notes and Annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML components, a ListOfEventAssignments container object may only contain EventAssignment objects.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12.4
21223.ShortMessage: Only EventAssignment, Notes and Annotation objects are allowed in ListOfEventAssignments

21224.Message:
A ListOfEventAssignments object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a ListOfEventAssignments object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21224.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the ListOfEventAssignments object

21225.Message:
An Event object must have the required attribute 'useValuesFromTriggerTime' and in addition may have the optional attributes 'metaid', 'sboTerm', 'id',  and 'name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an Event object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21225.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the Event object

21226.Message:
A Trigger object must have the required attributes 'persistent' and 'initialValue', and in addition, may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Trigger object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21226.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the Trigger object

21227.Message:
A Delay object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Delay object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21227.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the Delay object

21228.Message:
The attribute 'persistent' on a Trigger object must have a value of type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21228.ShortMessage: The Trigger attribute 'persistent' must evaluate to a Boolean value

21229.Message:
The attribute 'initialValue' on a Trigger object must have a value of type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21229.ShortMessage: The Trigger attribute 'initialValue' must evaluate to a Boolean value

21230.Message:
An Event object may contain at most one Priority object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21230.ShortMessage: An Event object can only have one Priority subobject

21231.Message:
An Priority object must contain exactly one MathML <math> element.  The <math> element is optional in L3V2 and beyond.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21231.ShortMessage: A Priority object may have one <math> element

21232.Message:
A Priority object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a Priority object.
Reference: L3V1 Section 4.12
21232.ShortMessage: Invalid attribute found on the Priority object

80501.Message: As a principle of best modeling practice, the size of a <compartment> should be set to a value rather than be left undefined. Doing so improves the portability of models between different simulation and analysis systems, and helps make it easier to detect potential errors in models.

1010101.Message:
To conform to Version 1 of the Hierarchical Model Composition package specification for SBML Level 3, an SBML document must declare the use of the following XML Namespace: 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/comp/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.1
1010101.ShortMessage: The comp ns is not correctly declared

1010102.Message:
Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Hierarchical Model Composition package must be declared either implicitly or explicitly to be in the XML namespace 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/comp/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.1

1010301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core specification.) Within a <model> or <modelDefinition> object, the values of the attributes id and comp:id on every instance of the following classes of objects must be unique across the set of all id and comp:id attribute values of all such objects in a model: the model itself, plus all contained <functionDefinition>, <compartment>, <species>, <reaction>, <speciesReference>, <modifierSpeciesReference>, <event>, and <parameter> objects, plus the <submodel> and <deletion> objects defined by the Hierarchical Model Composition package, plus any objects defined by any other package with 'package:id' attributes defined as falling in the 'SId' namespace.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.9

1010302.Message:
The values of the attributes 'id' and 'comp:id' on every instance of all <model>, <modelDefinition>, and <externalModelDefinition> objects must be unique across the set of all 'id' and 'comp:id' attribute values of such objects in the SBML document to which they belong.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.9
1010302.ShortMessage: Model and ExternalModelDefinitions must have unique ids

1010303.Message:
Within <model> and <modelDefinition> objects inside an SBML document, the value of the attribute 'comp:id' on every instance of a <port> object must be unique across the set of all 'comp:id' attribute values of all such objects in the model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.9

1010304.Message:
The value of a comp:id attribute must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.1.7

1010308.Message:

Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1010311.Message:
The value of a 'comp:name' attribute must always conform to the syntax of type string.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 3.1.1

If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, the units of the replaced element, multiplied by the units of any applicable conversion factor, should equal the units of the replacement element.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5

In all SBML documents using the HierarchicalModel Composition package, the SBML object must include a value for the attribute 'comp:required' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2

The value of attribute 'comp:required' on the SBML object must be of the data type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2

The value of attribute 'comp:required' on the SBML object must be set to 'true' if the Model object within the SBML object contains any Submodel with Species, Parameter, Compartment, Reaction, or Event objects that have not been either directly or indirectly replaced.

1020204.ShortMessage: The comp:required attribute must be 'false' if math does not change

1020205.Message:

Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020208.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfExternalModelDefinitions> container may only contain <externalModelDefinition> objects.

Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020210.Message:
A <listOfExternalModelDefinitions> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfExternalModelDefinitions> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020211.Message:
There may be at most one instance of the <listOfExternalModelDefinitions> within an SBML object that uses the SBML Level 3 Hierarchical Model Composition package.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3

1020212.Message:
The value of attribute 'comp:required' on the SBML object must be set to 'true'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.1

1020301.Message:
An <externalModelDefinition> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'.  No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <externalModelDefinition> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.2

1020302.Message:
An <externalModelDefinition> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotation.  No other subobjects from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Hierarchical Model Composition namespace are permitted on an <externalModelDefinition> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2

1020303.Message:
An <externalModelDefinition> object must have the attributes 'comp:id' and 'comp:source', and may have the optional attributes 'comp:name', 'comp:modelRef', and 'comp:md5'. No other attributes from the Hierarchical Model Composition namespace are permitted on an <externalModelDefinition> object.

1020304.Message:
The value of the 'comp:source' attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must reference an SBML Level 3 Version 1 document.

1020305.Message:
The value of the 'comp:modelRef' attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must be the value of an id attribute on a <model>, <modelDefinition>, or <externalModelDefinition> object in the SBML document referenced by the 'comp:source' attribute.

1020306.Message:

The value of a 'comp:source' attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must always conform to the syntax of the XML Schema 1.0 data type 'anyURI'.

1020308.Message:
The value of a comp:modelRef attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2
1020308.ShortMessage: The 'comp:modelRef' attribute must have the syntax of 'SId'

1020309.Message:
The value of a comp:md5 attribute on an <externalModelDefinition> object must always conform to the syntax of type string.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.3.2
1020309.ShortMessage: The 'comp:md5' attribute must have the syntax of 'string'

1020501.Message:

1020504.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfPorts> container object may only contain <port> objects.

1020505.Message:
A <listOfSubmodels> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfSubmodels> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4

1020506.Message:
A <listOfPorts> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <listOfPorts> object.

1020601.Message:

1020604.Message:

1020605.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfDeletions> container object may only contain <deletion> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5

1020606.Message:

1020614.Message:

1020617.ShortMessage: <model> may not reference <submodel> that references itself.

1020622.Message:

1020623.Message:

1020707.Message:

1020712.Message:
An <sBaseRef> object must point to another object; that is, a <sBaseRef> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.

1020712.ShortMessage: An SBaseRef must reference an object.

1020713.Message:
An <sBaseRef> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <sBaseRef> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020713.ShortMessage: An SBaseRef must reference only one other object.

1020714.Message:
Any one SBML object may only be referenced in one of the following ways:  referenced by a single <port> object; referenced by a single <deletion> object; referenced by a single <replacedElement>; be the parent of a single <replacedBy> child; be referenced by one or more <replacedBy> objects; or be referenced by one or more <replacedElement> objects all using the 'deletion' attribute.  Essentially, once an object has been referenced in one of these ways it cannot be referenced again.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.7.1
1020714.ShortMessage: Objects may not be referenced by mutiple SBaseRef constructs.

1020801.Message:
A <port> object must point to another object; that is, a <port> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4.3

1020802.Message:
A <port> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <port> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4.3
1020802.ShortMessage: Port must reference only one other object.

1020803.Message:

Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4.3

1020804.Message:
Port definitions must be unique; that is, no two <port> objects in a given Model may reference the same object in that Model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.4.3

1020901.Message:
A <deletion> object must point to another object; that is, a <deletion> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.3

1020902.Message:
A <deletion> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <deletion> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', or 'comp:metaIdRef'
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.3
1020902.ShortMessage: Deletion must reference only one other object.

1020903.Message:
A <deletion> object must have a value for one, and only one, of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', and 'comp:metaIdRef'.  It may also have the optional attributes 'comp:id' and 'comp:name'.  No other attributes from the Hierarchical Model Composition namespace are permitted on a <deletion> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.5.3

1021001.Message:
A <replacedElement> object must point to another object; that is, a <replacedElement> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', 'comp:metaIdRef' or 'comp:deletion'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1021002.Message:
A <replacedElement> object can only point to one other object; that is, a given <replacedElement> object can only have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', 'comp:metaIdRef' or 'comp:deletion'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2
1021002.ShortMessage: ReplacedElement must reference only one other object.

1021003.Message:
A <replacedElement> object must have a value for the required attribute 'comp:submodelRef', and a value for one, and only one, of the following attributes: 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef', 'comp:metaIdRef', or 'comp:deletion'. It may also have a value for the optional attribute 'comp:conversionFactor'. No other attributes from the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <replacedElement> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1021004.Message:
The value of a 'comp:submodelRef' attribute on a <replacedElement> object must be the identifier of a <submodel> present in the <replacedElement> object's parent Model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2
1021004.ShortMessage: The 'comp:submodelRef' attribute must point to a <submodel>

1021005.Message:
The value of a 'comp:deletion' attribute on a <replacedElement> object must be the identifier of a <deletion> present in the <replacedElement> object's parent Model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2
1021005.ShortMessage: The 'comp:deletion' attribute must point to a <deletion>

1021006.Message:
The value of a 'comp:conversionFactor' attribute on a <replacedElement> object must be the identifier of a <parameter> present in the <replacedElement> object's parent Model
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2
1021006.ShortMessage: The 'comp:conversionFactor attribute must point to a <parameter>

1021010.Message:
No two <replacedElement> objects in the same Model may reference the same object unless that object is a <deletion>
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1021011.Message:
If a <replacedElement> uses the 'comp:deletion' attribute, then it should not also use the 'comp:conversionFactor' attribute.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.2

1021101.Message:
A <replacedBy> object must point to another object; that is, a <replacedBy> object must always have a value for one of the attributes 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef' or 'comp:metaIdRef'.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.4

1021102.Message:

Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.4
1021102.ShortMessage: ReplacedBy must reference only one other object.

1021103.Message:
A <replacedBy> object must have a value for the required attribute 'comp:submodelRef', and a value for one, and only one, of the following attributes: 'comp:portRef', 'comp:idRef', 'comp:unitRef' or 'comp:metaIdRef'. No other attributes from the HierarchicalModel Composition namespace are permitted on a <replacedElement> object.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.4

1021104.Message:
The value of a 'comp:submodelRef' attribute on a <replacedBy> object must be the identifier of a <submodel> present in the <replacedBy> object's parent Model.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.4
1021104.ShortMessage: The 'comp:submodelRef' attribute must point to a <submodel>

1021201.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, the SBML class of the replacement element must match the SBML class of the replaced element, with two exceptions: an element of a derived class may replace an object of its base class (for base classes other than SBase), and any SBML class with mathematical meaning may replace a <parameter>. A base class may not replace a derived class, however, nor may a <parameter> replace some other SBML element with mathematical meaning.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5

1021202.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, if the replaced element has the 'id' attribute set, the replacement !element must also have the 'id' attribute set.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5
1021202.ShortMessage: Replaced IDs must be replaced with IDs.

1021203.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, if the replaced element has the 'metaid' attribute set, the replacement element must also have the 'metaid' attribute set.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5
1021203.ShortMessage: Replaced metaids must be replaced with metaids.

1021204.Message:
If one element replaces another, whether it is the target of a <replacedBy> element, or whether it has a child <replacedElement>, if the replaced element has an identifier attribute from some other SBML package set, the replacement element must also have that same identifier attribute set.
Reference: L3V1 Comp V1 Section 3.6.5
1021204.ShortMessage: Replaced package IDs must be replaced with package IDs.

2010101.Message:
To conform to Version 1 of the Flux Balance Constraints package specification for SBML Level 3, an SBML document must declare the use of the following XML Namespace: 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/fbc/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.1
2010101.ShortMessage: The fbc ns is not correctly declared

2010102.Message:
Wherever they appear in an SBML document, elements and attributes from the Flux Balance Constraints package must be declared either implicitly or explicitly to be in the XML namespace 'http://www.sbml.org/sbml/level3/version1/fbc/version1'
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.1

2010301.Message:
(Extends validation rule #10301 in the SBML Level 3 Version 1 Core specification.) Within a <model> object the values of the attributes id and fbc:id on every instance of the following classes of objects must be unique across the set of all id and fbc:id attribute values of all such objects in a model: the model itself, plus all contained <functionDefinition>, <compartment>, <species>, <reaction>, <speciesReference>, <modifierSpeciesReference>, <event>, and <parameter> objects, plus the <fluxBound>, <objective>, <fluxObjective>, <geneProduct> and <geneProductAssociation> objects defined by the Flux Balance Constraints package.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.2

2010302.Message:
The value of a fbc:id attribute must always conform to the syntax of the SBML data type SId.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.2

2020101.Message:
In all SBML documents using the Flux Balance Constraints package, the SBML object must include a value for the attribute 'fbc:required.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2

2020102.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:required' on the SBML object must be of the data type Boolean.
Reference: L3V1 Core Section 4.1.2
2020102.ShortMessage: The fbc:required attribute must be Boolean

2020103.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:required' on the SBML object must be set to 'false'.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.1

2020201.Message:
There may be at most one instance of each of the following kinds of objects within a <model> object using Flux Balance Constraints: <listOfFluxBounds> (V1 only), <listOfObjectives> and <listOfGeneProducts> (V2).
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3
2020201.ShortMessage: One of each list of allowed

2020202.Message:
The various ListOf subobjects with a <model> object are optional, but if present, these container object must not be empty. Specifically, if any of the following classes of objects are present on the <model>, it must not be empty: <listOfFluxBounds> (V1 only), <listOfObjectives> and <listOfGeneProducts> (V2).
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020203.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfFluxBounds> container object may only contain <fluxBound> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020204.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfObjectives> container object may only contain <objective> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020205.Message:
A <listOfFluxBounds> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <listOfFluxBounds> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020206.Message:
A <listOfFluxBounds> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. Additionally the <listOfObjectives> must contain the attribute 'activeObjective'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <listOfFluxBounds> object. 
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.3

2020207.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:activeObjective' on the <listOfObjectives> object must be of the data type SIdRef.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.2.2

2020208.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:activeObjective' on the <listOfObjectives> object must be the identifier of an existing <objective>.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.2.2

2020209.Message: A <model> object must have the required attributes 'strict'. No other attributes from the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <model> object.

2020210.Message: The attribute 'fbc:strict' on the <model> object must have a value of datatype Boolean.

2020211.Message: Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfGeneProducts> container object may only contain <geneProduct> objects.

2020212.Message: A <listOfGeneProducts> object may have the optional attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <listOfGeneProducts> object.

2020301.Message:
A SBML <species> object may have the optional attributes 'fbc:charge' and 'fbc:chemicalFormula'. No other attributes from the Flux Balance Constraints namespaces are permitted on a <species>. 
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.4

2020302.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:charge' on SBML <species> object must be of the data type integer.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.4

2020303.Message:
The value of attribute 'fbc:chemicalFormula' on the SBML <species> object must be set to a string consisting only of atomic names or user defined compounds and their occurrence.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.4

2020401.Message:
A <fluxBound> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <fluxBound>.
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020401.ShortMessage: <fluxBound> may only have 'metaId' and 'sboTerm' from L3 namespace

2020402.Message:
A <fluxBound> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <fluxBound>.
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020402.ShortMessage: <fluxBound> may only have <notes> and <annotations> from L3 Core

2020403.Message:
A <fluxBound> object must have the required attributes 'fbc:reaction', 'fbc:operation' and 'fbc:value', and may have the optional attributes 'fbc:id' and 'fbc:name'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <fluxBound> object.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5

2020404.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:reaction' of a <fluxBound> must be of the data type SIdRef.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5

2020405.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:name' of a <fluxBound> must be of the data type string.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5
2020405.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:name' must be of the data type string

2020406.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:operation' of a <fluxBound> must be of the data type FbcOperation and thus it's value must be one of 'lessEqual', 'greaterEqual' or 'equal'.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5
2020406.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:operation' must be of data type FbcOperation

2020407.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:value' of a <fluxBound> must be of the data type double.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5
2020407.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:value' must be of the data type double

2020408.Message:
The value of the attribute 'fbc:reaction' of a <fluxBound> object must be the identifier of an existing <reaction> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5

2020409.Message:
The combined set of all <fluxBound>'s with identical values for 'fbc:reaction' must be consistent. That is while it is possible to define a lower and an upper bound for a reaction, it is not possible to define multiple lower or upper bounds.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1 Section 3.5

2020501.Message:

2020501.ShortMessage: <objective> may only have 'metaId' and 'sboTerm' from L3 namespace

2020502.Message:
An <objective> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on an <objective>.

2020504.Message:
The attribute 'fbc:name' on an <objective> must be of the data type 'string'.

2020504.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:name' must be of the data type string

2020505.Message:

2020506.Message:

2020507.Message:
The <listOfFluxObjectives> subobject within an <objective> object must not be empty.

2020508.Message:
Apart from the general notes and annotation subobjects permitted on all SBML objects, a <listOfFluxObjectives> container object may only contain <fluxObjective> objects.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6

2020509.Message:
A <listOfFluxObjectives> object may have the optional 'metaid' and 'sboTerm' defined by SBML Level 3 Core. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace or the Flux Balance Constraints namespace are permitted on a <listOfFluxObjectives> object
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.6
2020509.ShortMessage: <listOfFluxObjectives> may only have 'metaId' and 'sboTerm' from L3 core

2020601.Message:
A <fluxObjective> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core attributes 'metaid' and 'sboTerm'. No other attributes from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <fluxObjective>.

2020601.ShortMessage: <fluxObjective> may only have 'metaId' and 'sboTerm' from L3 namespace

2020602.Message:
A <fluxObjective> object may have the optional SBML Level 3 Core subobjects for notes and annotations. No other elements from the SBML Level 3 Core namespace are permitted on a <fluxObjective>.
Reference: L3V1 Core, Section 3.2
2020602.ShortMessage: <fluxObjective> may only have <notes> and <annotations> from L3 Core

2020604.Message:

2020604.ShortMessage: The attribute 'fbc:name' must be of the data type string

2020605.Message:

2020606.Message:
The value of the attribute 'fbc:reaction' of a <fluxObjective> object must be the identifier of an existing <reaction> object defined in the enclosing <model> object.
Reference: L3V1 Fbc V1, Section 3.7

2020607.Message:
The value of the attribute 'fbc:coefficient' of a <fluxObjective> object must conform to the syntax of the SBML data type 'double'.
